duck: Argentinosaurus is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur first discovered by Guillermo Heredia in Argentina.

}} 'Argentinosaurus' is a genus of titanosaur sauropod dinosaur first discovered
by Guillermo Heredia in Argentina. The generic name refers to the country in
which it was discovered. The dinosaur lived on the then-island continent of
South America somewhere between 97 and 94 million years ago, during the
Late Cretaceous Epoch.
